<subSubSection id="48D355CA8E78FFF648A7535FFB41F81C" pageId="54" pageNumber="55" type="description">
<paragraph id="007606418E78FFF648A7535FFB75F9AF" blockId="54.[151,1437,1139,2028]" pageId="54" pageNumber="55">
<emphasis id="32BDDA538E78FFF648A7535FFE0DFB7C" bold="true" box="[151,424,1139,1164]" pageId="54" pageNumber="55">Description of Female.</emphasis>
Fully winged; length 
<quantity id="C731ABA48E78FFF64A9C5358FC93FB7B" box="[684,822,1140,1164]" metricMagnitude="-3" metricUnit="m" metricValue="3.55" metricValueMax="3.9" metricValueMin="3.2" pageId="54" pageNumber="55" unit="mm" value="3.55" valueMax="3.9" valueMin="3.2">3.2–3.9 mm</quantity>
. Head black, except mandible and clypeus testaceous; antenna brown, except segment 2 and ventral side of segment 1 testaceous; mesosoma black; metasoma brown; legs testaceous, except one black small spot on club of profemur; mesocoxa with proximal margin black; metacoxa with proximal half black. Antenna clavate; antennal segments in following proportions: 9:6:19:14:12:9:8:7.5:7:9. Head shiny, smooth, punctate, unsculptured among punctures; vertex behind ocellar triangle weakly rugose; frontal line complete (in specimen from 
<collectingCountry id="78DE46D18E78FFF64A26520BFDF9FACF" box="[534,604,1319,1343]" name="China" pageId="54" pageNumber="55">China</collectingCountry>
, Xunyangkan Town, frontal line shortly interrupted in middle); occipital carina complete; POL = 6; OL = 3; OOL = 12; OPL = 6; TL = 12. Scutum and scutellum shiny, smooth, punctate, unsculptured among punctures (in some specimens from 
<collectingCountry id="78DE46D18E78FFF64B075243FCD8FA77" box="[823,893,1391,1415]" name="China" pageId="54" pageNumber="55">China</collectingCountry>
, Xunyangkan Town, posterior third of scutum weakly rugose). Notauli incomplete, reaching approximately 0.5–0.7 length of scutum. Metanotum dull, rugose. Propodeum dull, reticulate rugose, without transverse or longitudinal keels. Fore wing hyaline, without dark transverse bands; occasionally fore wing slightly and completely darkened; distal part of stigmal vein shorter than proximal part (6:8). Protarsal segments in following proportions: 20:4:4:9:17. Enlarged claw (
<figureCitation id="98F21AC48E78FFF64C8A52D3FA8CF9E7" box="[1210,1321,1535,1559]" captionStart="PLATE 15" captionStartId="55.[151,233,1969,1992]" captionTargetBox="[157,1422,204,1938]" captionTargetId="figure-61@55.[151,1436,193,1949]" captionTargetPageId="55" captionText="PLATE 15. Fiorianteon junonium. A. Chela of female from Japan, Mt. Tsukuba (from Olmi 1995a). B, C. Holotype, dorsal view (B) and lateral view (C) (from Olmi 1984). Length 3.8 mm. Scale bar 0.20 mm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5278422" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/5278422/files/figure.png" pageId="54" pageNumber="55">Plate 15A</figureCitation>
) with one very small subapical tooth, without lamellae, bristles or hairs. Segment 5 of protarsus (
<figureCitation id="98F21AC48E78FFF64C585108FB72F9CC" box="[1128,1239,1572,1596]" captionStart="PLATE 15" captionStartId="55.[151,233,1969,1992]" captionTargetBox="[157,1422,204,1938]" captionTargetId="figure-61@55.[151,1436,193,1949]" captionTargetPageId="55" captionText="PLATE 15. Fiorianteon junonium. A. Chela of female from Japan, Mt. Tsukuba (from Olmi 1995a). B, C. Holotype, dorsal view (B) and lateral view (C) (from Olmi 1984). Length 3.8 mm. Scale bar 0.20 mm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5278422" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/5278422/files/figure.png" pageId="54" pageNumber="55">Plate 15A</figureCitation>
) with one row of approximately 37 small lamellae; distal apex with approximately 13 lamellae. Tibial spurs 1/1/2.
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="007606418E78FFF648F75147FB41F81C" blockId="54.[151,1437,1139,2028]" pageId="54" pageNumber="55">
<emphasis id="32BDDA538E78FFF648F75147FE64F974" bold="true" box="[199,449,1643,1668]" pageId="54" pageNumber="55">Description of Male.</emphasis>
Fully winged (
<figureCitation id="98F21AC48E78FFF64AB05140FCB0F974" box="[640,789,1644,1668]" captionStart="PLATE 15" captionStartId="55.[151,233,1969,1992]" captionTargetBox="[157,1422,204,1938]" captionTargetId="figure-61@55.[151,1436,193,1949]" captionTargetPageId="55" captionText="PLATE 15. Fiorianteon junonium. A. Chela of female from Japan, Mt. Tsukuba (from Olmi 1995a). B, C. Holotype, dorsal view (B) and lateral view (C) (from Olmi 1984). Length 3.8 mm. Scale bar 0.20 mm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5278422" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/5278422/files/figure.png" pageId="54" pageNumber="55">Plate 15B, C</figureCitation>
); length 
<quantity id="C731ABA48E78FFF64BB05140FBA8F973" box="[896,1037,1644,1668]" metricMagnitude="-3" metricUnit="m" metricValue="3.25" metricValueMax="3.8" metricValueMin="2.7" pageId="54" pageNumber="55" unit="mm" value="3.25" valueMax="3.8" valueMin="2.7">2.7–3.8 mm</quantity>
. Head black, except mandible and clypeus testaceous; antenna testaceous (in specimen from 
<collectingCountry id="78DE46D18E78FFF64B0251BCFCD1F957" box="[818,884,1680,1703]" name="Japan" pageId="54" pageNumber="55">Japan</collectingCountry>
, Uradani, antenna brown, except ventral side of segment 1 testaceous); mesosoma and metasoma black; legs testaceous, except basal region of metacoxa black; in specimen from 
<collectingCountry id="78DE46D18E78FFF6497951F4FE29F91F" box="[329,396,1752,1775]" name="Japan" pageId="54" pageNumber="55">Japan</collectingCountry>
, Uradani, metacoxa almost totally black. Antenna filiform; antennal segments in following proportions: 11:5:18:14:13:11:9:9:8:10. Head shiny, strongly punctate, unsculptured among punctures; frontal line complete; occipital carina complete; POL = 6; OL = 4; OOL = 11; OPL = 6; TL = 12. Scutum shiny, very strongly punctate, unsculptured among punctures (in some specimens from 
<collectingCountry id="78DE46D18E78FFF64BAB5068FC44F8AC" box="[923,993,1860,1884]" name="China" pageId="54" pageNumber="55">China</collectingCountry>
, Xunyangkan Town, posterior third of scutum weakly rugose). Notauli incomplete, reaching approximately 0.5–0.7 length of scutum. Scutellum punctate, unsculptured among punctures. Metanotum dull, rugose. Propodeum reticulate rugose, without transverse or longitudinal keels. Fore wing hyaline, without dark transverse bands; distal part of stigmal vein much shorter than proximal part (4:10). Paramere (
<figureCitation id="98F21AC48E78FFF64A3250F8FDC8F81C" box="[514,621,2004,2028]" captionStart="PLATE 14" captionStartId="52.[151,233,1880,1903]" captionTargetBox="[186,1399,215,1848]" captionTargetId="figure-105@52.[166,1421,195,1858]" captionTargetPageId="52" captionText="PLATE 14. A, C. Chelae, holotypes. B, D–F. Male genitalia. A. Conganteon taiwanense (from Olmi 1991). B. C. taiwanense from China, Nanling (from Olmi 1995a). C. Fiorianteon choui (from Olmi 1995a). D. F.choui, paratype (from Olmi 1995a). E. F.choui from China, Nanling. F. F. junonium, holotype (from Olmi 1984). Scale bar 0.09 mm for A, 0.30 mm for B, 0.20 mm for C, 0.24 mm for D, 0.26 mm for E and 0.31 mm for F." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5278418" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/5278418/files/figure.png" pageId="54" pageNumber="55">Plate 14F</figureCitation>
) without a deep notch in dorsal view. Tibial spurs 1/1/2.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<caption id="54B656C98E79FFF748A7509DFC52F816" ID-DOI="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5278422" ID-Zenodo-Dep="5278422" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/5278422/files/figure.png" pageId="55" pageNumber="56" startId="55.[151,233,1969,1992]" targetBox="[157,1422,204,1938]" targetPageId="55">
<paragraph id="007606418E79FFF748A7509DFC52F816" blockId="55.[151,1436,1969,2023]" pageId="55" pageNumber="56">
<emphasis id="32BDDA538E79FFF748A7509DFEB4F838" bold="true" box="[151,273,1969,1992]" pageId="55" pageNumber="56">PLATE 15.</emphasis>
<taxonomicName id="C7C97DC28E79FFF74929509FFE5CF838" authorityName="Olmi" authorityYear="1984" box="[281,505,1971,1992]" class="Insecta" family="Dryinidae" genus="Fiorianteon" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="55" pageNumber="56" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="junonium">
<emphasis id="32BDDA538E79FFF74929509FFE5CF838" box="[281,505,1971,1992]" italics="true" pageId="55" pageNumber="56">Fiorianteon junonium</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
. 
<emphasis id="32BDDA538E79FFF74A38509DFD85F838" bold="true" box="[520,544,1969,1992]" pageId="55" pageNumber="56">A.</emphasis>
Chela of female from Japan, Mt. Tsukuba (from 
<bibRefCitation id="64587BB08E79FFF74C11509EFB3EF838" author="Olmi, M." box="[1057,1179,1970,1992]" journalOrPublisher="Bollettino di Zoologia agraria e di Bachicoltura" pageId="55" pageNumber="56" pagination="19 - 34" part="27" refId="ref365706" refString="Olmi, M. (1995 a) A contribution to the knowledge of the Dryinidae of Taiwan (Hymenoptera Chrysidoidea). Bollettino di Zoologia agraria e di Bachicoltura, Ser. II, 27, 19 - 34." title="A contribution to the knowledge of the Dryinidae of Taiwan (Hymenoptera Chrysidoidea)" type="journal article" year="1995">Olmi 1995a</bibRefCitation>
). 
<emphasis id="32BDDA538E79FFF74C82509EFB4CF838" bold="true" box="[1202,1257,1969,1992]" pageId="55" pageNumber="56">B, C.</emphasis>
Holotype, dorsal view (
<emphasis id="32BDDA538E79FFF748E750FDFF4DF816" bold="true" box="[215,232,2001,2022]" pageId="55" pageNumber="56">B</emphasis>
) and lateral view (
